5 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Content of driving privilege card. A driving privilege card must contain:
6 (1) a full-face photograph of the person issued the card, in the size and form prescribed by the
7 department;
8 (2) a distinguishing number issued to the person by the department;
9 (3) the person's full legal name, date of birth, and Montana residence address, unless the person
10 requests the use of the person's mailing address;
11 (4) a brief description of the person;
12 (5) either the person's customary manual signature or a reproduction of the person's customary
13 manual signature;
14 (6) the issuance date and the expiration date of the driving privilege card;
15 (7) any endorsements or restrictions applicable to the person; and
16 (8) spaces for indicating whether the person has executed:
17 (a) a document under 72-17-201 of intent to make a gift of all or part of the driver's body under the
18 Uniform Anatomical Gift Act; or
19 (b) a declaration under 50-9-103 relating to the use of life-sustaining treatment.
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Administration of driving privilege card. County treasurers or other
22 qualified officers appointed by the department pursuant to 61-5-111 must be the department's agents for the
23 sale of driving privilege receipts.
24
25 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Revocation of driving privilege card. If the possessor of a driving
26 privilege card is in removal proceedings or has been ordered removed from the United States, the driving
27 privilege card is void and may be revoked by the motor vehicle division.
